.TH SERCON 1 "June 2026" "sercon" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sercon \- interactive serial console for Arduino and UART devices
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sercon
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sercon
connects your terminal to a serial device and forwards input/output in both
directions. It can list available serial ports, set baud rate, print timestamps
on incoming lines, and render ANSI styling when supported.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -l , " --list"
List available serial ports and exit.
.TP
.BR -h , " --help"
Show help text and exit.
.TP
.BR -p , " --port " PORT{:BAUD}
Serial port to open with optional baud-rate (default: 9600).
.TP
.BR -T , " --no-timestamps"
Disable timestamp prefix on incoming lines.
.TP
.BR -H , " --non-persistent-history"
Do not use history file.
.TP
.BR -e , " --max-history " MAX-ENTRIES
Set maximum number of history entries. Default: 0 (unlimited).
.TP
.BR -v , " --version"
Print version information and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
List ports:
.PP
.RS
.B sercon --list
.RE
.PP
Show help:
.PP
.RS
.B sercon --help
.RE
.PP
Connect at 9600 baud:
.PP
.RS
.B sercon --port cu.usbmodem1101
.RE
.PP
Disable timestamps:
.PP
.RS
.B sercon -p cu.usbmodem1101 --no-timestamps
.RE
.PP
Print version:
.PP
.RS
.B sercon --version
.RE
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGINT
Ctrl+C triggers graceful shutdown.
.SH BEHAVIOR NOTES
Prompt text defaults to the selected port basename (or the executable name).
.PP
Prompt and cursor UI are shown only in interactive mode with ANSI enabled.
.PP
Carriage returns are ignored, and linefeeds define line/timestamp boundaries.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful execution.
.TP
.B 1
Invalid arguments, missing required port, or serial open/read error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR stty (1),
.BR screen (1),
.BR picocom (1),
.BR minicom (1)
